CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 14, 1959, pg. A3, reads: "Part of the Crowd - Above is part of the crowd which witnessed the cornerstone laying at Loendi Club Sunday afternoon. The cornerstone itself was laid by a special team, as Masons from the western end of the state turned out en masse, together with members and friends of the organization."
TitMainTitle: Crowd gathered in front of six Masons wearing tuxedos and chain collars and van with American flag and loudspeakers, for cornerstone laying ceremony for Loendi Club on Ledlie Street, Hill District
